The paper deals with the task of visual question answering, which involves understanding both images and language. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Among these, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the visual and linguistic aspects of the task, respectively. However, the paper also discusses the use of ensemble methods and domain-invariant features, which are relevant to machine learning and information retrieval, respectively. Therefore, these categories are also possible.
